<h1>Evening Orders</h1>

<div class="docbody">
<div class="opener">
<table class="salutationBlock">
        <tr>
		<td class="salutationRight">[Winchester, 26 May 1756]</td>
	      </tr>
      </table>
</div>
<p style="text-indent: 0;">Evening Orders.</p>
<p>As many Draughts are expected up for the Regiment immediatelythe Commissary is to call in all the countrys arms, which he has delivered out of the Stores, upon receipts given to the people. If the people of the Town or Country, have any arms, clothes, Blankets, &amp;c. &amp;c. belonging to the Soldiers, which they have bought; they are desired to give them in immediately to the commanding officer: If they are found in their possession after issuing this order; they must expect to be prosecuted to the utmost rigour of the Law; which has laid a penalty
<span class="pb" title="page number in print edition (no page scan available)" id="GEWN-02-03-02-pb-0178">[178]</span>
of twenty pounds (upon any person who buys or exchanges any arms, Clothes &amp;c. with a Soldier;) to be paid to the Informer.<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-02-03-02-0178-fn-0001" id="GEWN-02-03-02-0178-fn-0001-ptr">1</a></p>
<p>The Commissary by the first conveyance to Conogochieg, is to send Captain Stewart, commanding Officer at that place, six axes, eight blankets, three bayonets, and twelve cartouch-boxes.</p>
</div>
<div class="docback">
<div class="note-source" id="GEWN-02-03-02-0178-sn">

   <p>
<abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Letter Book Copy: letters copied into a bound letter-book ]">LB</abbr>, <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ U.S. Library of Congress, George Washington Papers, Washington, D.C. ]">DLC:GW</span>.
</p>

</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-03-02-0178-fn-0001-ptr" id="GEWN-02-03-02-0178-fn-0001">1</a>

   <p>The act of 1755 imposing military discipline on the Virginia forces, what GW often called the military or mutiny act, provided that if any person shall knowingly buy or exchange, or otherwise receive any arms or cloaths from any soldier or deserter . . . the person so offending, shall forfeit . . . twenty pounds (6 <span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ William Waller Hening, ed. &lt;i&gt;The Statutes at Large; Being a Collection of All the Laws of Virginia, from the First Session of the Legislature, in the Year 1619&lt;/i&gt;. 13 vols. 181923. Reprint. Charlottesville, Va., 1969. ]">Hening</span> 55964). The Draughts referred to are those being drawn from the militia. See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-03-02-0171" class="document">Orders, 23 May 1756</a>.</p>

</div>
